headline.main: Europe; French Triangle a Key Piece in Hitler's War Game

lead_paragraph: France is still a weighty factor in the war. This is clear as the deadlock between Petain and Hitler nears its uncertain end. The position of Laval is said to be the issue, but Laval is only a pretext, a small symbol of the great questions involved in this strange contest of wills between the "old man of Vichy" and the "master of Europe."
